Given a connector with multiple task kinds and an attribute of type TYPE_TASK_DEPENDENCY.

The content assist for the dependency attribute editor lists all tasks for the given connector. Some connectors need to filter this list according to the field in question (eg. attribute can only reference one type of tasks from this connector). Right now, it involves heavy trickery to handle this (new attribute editor based on richtexteditor to reuse content assist logic, unconfigure/reconfigure text viewer to inject own content assist and references to internal classes like @TaskCompletionProposal@). For the given usecase, I think it would make sense to add a new @TaskAttributeMapper#getTaskProposals@ which, by default, returns all tasks but can be filtered by overriding it. The content assist in  @RepositoryCompletionProcessor@ should then ask the mapper of the connector for the relevant tasks. For API and simplicity, I'd suggest to let the connector only handle with ITasks instead of TaskCompletionProposal. Something along the lines of 
@protected Set<ITask> getTaskProposals(TaskAttribute attribute)@

The task activity viewer aggregates activity information from various sources. The activity should be stored in a data model that can be cached and indexed. Proposal for the ActivityRecord data model:

ActivityRecord {

 // time the event happened, e.g. a change set was committed
 Data date; 

 List<IIdentity> people;

 List<IResource> resources;

 // unique handle identifier, uri?
 String handle;

 // identifies the source of the contribution
 String kind;

 // related task
 ITask task;

}

We'll also need a notification mechanism but that maybe more suitable on the provider level.

